  "text": "In this paper we study the problem of visual analogies for natural images and show the first results of its kind on solving visual analogy questions for natural images. Our proposed method learns an embedding where similarities are transferable across pairs of analogous images using a Siamese network architecture. We introduce Visual Analogy Question Answering (VAQA), a dataset of natural images that can be used to generate analogies across different objects attributes and actions of animals. We also compile a large set of analogy questions using the 3D chair dataset [CITATION_1] containing analogies across viewpoint and style. Our experimental evaluations show promising results on solving visual analogy questions. We explore different kinds of analogies with various numbers of distracters, and show generalization to unseen analogies.",
